			<ns0:name>b...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105821748722532785568/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Subprocess launching tests need to be in the NaCl code base.  this needs to be exercised using sel_universal, which has a ReverseEmulate object for providing reverse service connections.

The SelLdrLauncherStandalone interface is not directly usable for launching subprocesses, since descriptors in use -- such as the command channel connection in sel_universal -- would get inherited by any additional subprocesses.  This causes a sel_universal analogy of the browser surf-away problem: the sel_ldr subprocess will not shut down, since the shutdown-when-the-command-channel-connection-closes semantics does not work when the command channel connection got inherited into the subprocess.

Since chrome uses the zygote process launcher architecture already, sel_universal probably should just follow.  That is, a zygote process is spawned early by sel_universal, and a zygote-representative object is a factory for creating SelLdrLauncherStandalone(-like) objects that proxy the process launching to the zygote.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-03-20T17:20:37.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2013-02-25T22:32:48.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>New</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
